borate the theoretical\nprediction by Sakaue's theory [Polymers 8(12), 424 (2016)] that there should\nnot be bias dependence of $\\beta$ for asymptotically long polymers. By\nexcluding fluctuations we also show that monomer crowding at the pore exit\ncannot have a measurable effect on translocation dynamics under realistic\nconditions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 20 Jul 2017 18:05:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 7 Dec 2017 11:11:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 15 Dec 2017 11:25:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-18"}
